# Instructions

### Create a configuration file with 5 mandatory parts.

|       Key        | Format                      | Description                       | Constraints |
| :--------------- | :-------------------------- | :-------------------------------- | :---------- |
| **`nb_drones`**  | `n` Positive integer        | Defines the number of drones.     | Must be the first line of the file. |
| **`start_hub`**  | `name` `x` `y` `[metadata]` | Defines the drone departure zone. | Must be unique. The name must contain no spaces or hyphens. x and y must be integers. |
| **`end_hub`**    | `name` `x` `y` `[metadata]` | Defines the drone arrival zone.   | Must be unique. The name must contain no spaces or hyphens. x and y must be integers. |
| **`hub`**        | `name` `x` `y` `[metadata]` | Defines all other zones.          | Coordinates and names must be unique. The name must contain no spaces or hyphens. x and y must be integers. |
| **`connection`** | `hub_a-hub_b`               | Defines links between zones.      | Hubs must be pre-defined. Avoid duplicates (A-B is the same as B-A). |


#### Metadata requirements
Defines zone or connection specificities. Each `key=value` must be separated by a space, enclosed in brackets.
|      Hub Key      | Value                                         | Default | Description                 |
| :---------------- | :-------------------------------------------- | :------ | :-----------------------    |
| **`zone=`**       | `normal`, `priority`, `restricted`, `blocked` | normal  | Define the type of the hub  |
| **`color=`**      | a single word (e.g., `red`, `blue`)           | None    | Define the color of the hub |
| **`max_drones=`** | positive integer                              | 1       | Define the maximum capacity |

|       Connection Key     | Value            | Default | Description                 |
| :----------------------  | :--------------- | :------:| :-----------------------    |
| **`max_link_capacity=`** | positive integer | 1       | Define the capacity maximal of the connection |


### Environment requirements
This project requires matplotlib and numpy.
Before running the program, you need to set up a virtual environment and install the necessary dependencies:
```bash
make install
```

### ▶️ Running the Program
To run the program using the first 0*.txt file located in the root directory:
```bash
make run
```

To run the program with a specific configuration file:
```bash
make run CONFIG=name_of_the_file.txt
```

